  "texts": [
    "Tan (2022) discusses if human explanations are suitable as additional supervision or as ground truth, given that humans can also provide explanations for incorrect labels.",
    "They point out that human explanations for most tasks are necessarily incomplete and do not present valid and complete reasoning paths.",
    "The doubts are supported by evidence that models mimic human misconceptions (Lin et al., 2022), which will likely affect generated explanations.",
    "Turpin et al. (2023) show with prompts containing surface biases that affect the predictions that this bias is never reflected in the explanations.",
    "Herman (2017) emphasizes the importance of differentiating between descriptive and persuasive explanations."
  ],
